metadata.name: Upside Down Bird
metadata.description:
2013.3.3
Upside Down Crow
3264x4928

On a foggy day in Seattle, while photographing the Space Needle (blurred in background), I noticed this crow looking at me, hanging from a branch, upside down.  What a perspective.

Even when I'm focused on a subject, I always keep my eyes on a swivel to catch the "moments in-between".  Kind of hard to do with just one functioning eye, but I've gotten used to it over the years.  I also thought it was neat how this bird was staring at me through one eye as the other appears to be blocked by a branch. 

- Ro
